I am trying to associate a custom event to deal object using <https://knowledge.HubSpot.com/analytics-tools/create-custom-behavioral-events-with-the-code-wizard#:~:text=to%20HubSpot.-,Create%20a%20Javascript%20code%20snippet,-Creating%20events%20with|Javascript code snippet>. I selected deals when I created the event (see screenshot), but I don't know how to edit the javascript code to specify a deal ID. According to doc there is only <https://developers.HubSpot.com/docs/api/events/tracking-code#:~:text=describe%20parameters%20/%20fields-,ARGUMENTS,defined%20properties%20and%20go%20back%20to%20create%20them%20after%20event%20tracking.,-Customize%20your%20tracking|2 attributes: 'name' and 'properties'> I tried to pass a `objectId` attribute like this but it didn't work. I get "Unknown user" in the deal name column. No deal is associated to the event.

```const currentUrl = window.location.href;
const pathname = new URL(currentUrl).pathname;

if (pathname == "/consentement-formulaire-inscription") {
_hsq.push([
  'trackCustomBehavioralEvent',
  {
    name: "pe7301089_consentement_formulaire_inscription",
    objectId: '9145575567',
    properties: {},
  },
]);
}```
